<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-23T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-23T23:00:00-05:00" n="436" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2449: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-24T12:00:00+08:00">October 24,
                                1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 24—1:43 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>606. China Customs [head] L. K. Little, having transferred headquarters here,
                        had long talk Generalissimo latter’s request—who, although claiming
                        unofficial status, proceeded give orders. Generalissimo seriously worried
                        over danger invasion Formosa and wants customs boat for defense.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>